<p>CADU seeks to consolidate itself as one of the industry leaders in the adoption of environmental protection
  practices, therefore, none of its land banks are located within protected areas or zones with high biodiversity
  value. The Company not only fully complies with the current environmental regulations, it also has programs
  that distinguish it as a pioneer in the subject.</p>

<p>CADU is subject to several environmental regulations, whose provisions are fully complied with, including the The Ley General del Equilibrio Ecologico y
  la Proteccion al Ambiente (General Law of Ecological Balance and Environmental Protection, known as LGEEPA for its Spanish acronym), which is Mexico's
  primary legal framework regarding environmental protection at a federal level. In the cases of areas where real estate developments
  could affect coastal ecosystems, the regulations of the Secretaria del Medio Ambiente y Recursos Naturales (Ministry of Environment and Natural
  Resources, known as SEMARNAT by its Spanish acronym) are enforced. As of today, no ecological fine or penalty from relevant authorities or any
  stakeholder have been imposed on CADU for failing to comply with environmental regulations.</p>

<h4>Environmental Performance</h4>

<p>CADU is mindful of the importance of the appropriate use of existing natural resources, such as water, electricity or land, since the efficient
  utilization of these resources helps to reduce the direct and indirect environmental impacts in the communities where it operates, and also at global scale.</p>

<p>For this reason, water care and saving are primordial elements in CADU's operations. The Company has never dumped wastes in aquifers such as rivers,
  lagoons and seas, and, as of today, no spillage that could have affected water bodies has occurred at any of its housing developments.</p>

<p>CADU incorporates the following programs and features in its developments:</p>
<ul class="c-content-list-1 c-theme c-separator-dot">
<li>Approval of HIPOTECA VERDE (Green Mortgage), a Federal Government program that prioritizes water and energy savings, as well as thermic insulation.</li>
<li>Use of energetical saving and CO2 emission reduction ecotechnologies.</li>
<li>DEEVi<sup>1</sup> and HEEVi<sup>2</sup> certifications in ECOCASA<sup>3</sup> programs.</li>
<li>Significant reduction of water and energy consumption by installing water-saving toilets, water-saving faucets for kitchen and bathroom,
  energy-saving lamps, thermal insulation and ecological showers.</li>
<li>VIVEROS (tree nurseries) program, which help the reproduction of species for their reintegration into the environment while deploying reforestation programs each year in the communities where the Company operates.</li>
</ul>

